# AI-generated code marker

When you (the AI assistant) **create a brand-new Swift file from scratch** or **substantially rewrite the body of a view / view model / service**, prepend this header right after the file copyright/import block:

```swift
// MARK: - AI-Generated, needs human review
//
// Created by Cursor on YYYY-MM-DD
// Reason: <short reason — "initial implementation", "refactor to IVO", etc.>
//
// TODO: review carefully, then remove this header.
```

## When to add the marker (by action, not by percentage)
ADD when:
- Creating a new file from scratch.
- Rewriting the whole `var body` of a SwiftUI view.
- Replacing the bulk of a view model / service implementation.

DO NOT add when:
- Fixing typos or renaming symbols.
- Adding 1–5 lines.
- Tweaking a single modifier or property.

## Rules
- Use a real ISO date (today's date), not a placeholder.
- The user uses `rg "AI-Generated, needs human review"` to track unreviewed files.

## Why
The developer is learning iOS and explicitly wants to avoid blind "vibe coding".
This marker is a personal technical-debt tracker, not a security feature.
